						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar near the northern entrance into the Mallēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kṛishṇarāya, 1516 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">yuva, Phālguṇa śu. 5,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1516 A.D. February 8, (Friday).</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to record a <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi> gift made by Rāyasam Koṇḍamarusu in the village Koṇḍapalli of Konḍavīṭi-rājya at the instance of the king.</p>						

						</summary>
